The National Engineering and Technical Company Limited (NETCO’s), subsidiary of the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC), has announced a total profit before tax of N6.75 billion in 2018 which represents an increase of 107 per cent from N3.26bn in 2017. In his statement to shareholders at the 29th Annual General Meeting (AGM) in Abuja yesterday, the chairman of the company, Mallam Bello Rabiu said the company was able to record the impressive performance in 2018 despite the challenges faced in the industry. At the AGM where the company’s annual report and audited accounts was presented, Mallam Rabiu said the company’s revenue also rose by 63 per cent (N2.68bn) from N22.46bn in 2017 to N36.64bn in 2018. He said the operating profit of the company increased by 130 percent from N2.07bn in the previous year to N4.75bn in the year under review. Owing to the leap in profit performance, according to Rabiu, NECTO overshot its last year’s highest dividend record of N750 million and the company declared a dividend of N1.50bn to its shareholders at the meeting. He said that the leap was an increase of 100 percent dividend from the previous year. The chairman attributed the achievements in 2018 to two major projects: Mobil Producing Nigeria (MPN) Major Integrity Projects (MIPs) EPCm2 and NPDC FPSO Mystras Operations & Maintenance Contract. The Managing Director of NETCO Engr. Mustapha Yakubu in his management report said the company had set a target to perform 660,000 man-hour of work.  Cutix Plc records outstanding performance in 2017 Nahco to raise N25bn capital, targets power sector, others Sokoto Cement records N1.92bn profit after tax Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin